description.narrative: During 2021, CAP (along with strategic partners) has played a leading role in highlighting critical child-rights issues. It was at the forefront of shaping public discourse on relevant issues, helping position UNICEF as the leading voice and advocate for all children in Rwanda.Partnerships with the extractive, rice, telecom and banking sectors have taken off, reaching the most vulnerable. CAP has engaged various government and non-government bodies to strengthen its foundational work as it aims to expand the private sector engagement to more sectors in 2022.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/01/2022
